%h2{:style => "text-align: center"} $5,000 for Bloggers Covering B.C. Municipal Elections

%div{:style => "margin-left: 10%; margin-right: 10%;"}

  %p
    British Columbia municipal elections will take place on November 19, 2011. Nomination deadline is October 14.
  %p
    To encourage better voter information,
    = link_to("VoterMedia.org", "/about_contact")
    is offering up to $5,000 in cash awards for blogs covering elections in 5 municipalities --
    up to $1,000 each for 5 blog competitions covering:
    %ul
      %strong
        %li= link_to("Burnaby", "/burnaby")
        %li= link_to("North Vancouver", "/northvan")
        %li= link_to("Richmond", "/richmondbc")
        %li= link_to("Surrey", "/surreybc")
        %li= link_to("West Vancouver", "/westvan")
  %p
    The competition judges will be the public --
    anyone who votes on each city's votermedia.org ballot linked above.
    As you can see on the linked ballots, voters allocate award shares to the contestants.
    Votes are tallied as described in the
    = link_to("Voting FAQ", "/faqs#Voting") + "."
  %p
    In each contest, we plan to award up to $20 per day for 50 days, starting October 1.
    There is no entry fee or entry deadline, but voting has already started
    so the sooner you enter the better. Detailed rules are below.
  %p
    We have been running votermedia competitions at UBC's student union for the past 5 years.
    For more info on how it works, see the videos at
    = link_to("votermedia.org", "/")
    and our
    = link_to("publications", "/publications")
    (especially "Global Voter Media Platform").
  %p
    To enter your blog in this competition,
    please copy and paste all the text between the horizontal lines below into an email,
    fill in all the blanks and send it to Mark Latham (mark[at]votermedia.org).
    (We're also happy to add blogs and ballot pages for other municipalities, without funded contests.)
  %p
    %strong
      Related links:
      %ul
        %li= link_to('Twitter: #bcmuni2011', 'http://twitter.com/#!/search/%23bcmuni2011')
        %li= link_to('VoterMedia Democracy Blog > Municipal', 'http://votermedia.blogspot.com/search/label/Municipal')
        %li= link_to('BC Civic Vote 2011', 'https://bc.civicvote.ca/') + ' - a new website on BC municipal elections'

